# Incident Report: Brute Force Login Attack

## Incident Summary

Multiple failed Windows authentication attempts were detected on the monitored endpoint. The activity exceeded the configured detection threshold and triggered a Microsoft Sentinel analytics rule for potential brute-force activity.

---

## Incident Information

| Field | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Incident Name | Brute Force Login Detection |
| Severity | Medium |
| Event ID | 4625 |
| Detection Source | Microsoft Sentinel |
| Data Source | Windows Security Logs |
| Affected Machine | SOC-WIN10-01 |
| Status | Investigated |

---

## Detection Logic

The analytics rule monitors Windows Security Event ID **4625**. If five or more failed authentication attempts occur within a five-minute window, Microsoft Sentinel generates an alert.

---

