- Logon type
- Source workstation
- Authentication package

---

## Investigation

The investigation confirmed repeated authentication failures using invalid credentials. No successful login was observed immediately after the failed attempts.

No evidence of privilege escalation or persistence techniques was identified during the investigation.

---

## MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

| Tactic | Technique | Technique ID |
|----------|-----------|--------------|
| Credential Access | Brute Force | T1110 |

---

## Impact Assessment

No unauthorized access was observed. However, repeated authentication failures may indicate password guessing or credential-based attacks.

---

## Recommended Response

- Investigate the source of the authentication attempts.
- Reset passwords if compromise is suspected.
- Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA).
- Monitor the account for additional authentication attempts.

---

## Lessons Learned

Repeated failed authentication attempts are one of the earliest indicators of brute-force attacks. Monitoring Event ID 4625 enables early detection and response.
